rom UMD and a Bachelor s Degree from Wittenberg University  She was previously an assistant professor at the Department of Public Policy at the Central European University and a visiting assistant professor at Washington and Lee University s Economics Department  Her teaching and research focuses on economics of institutions  post socialist economies and politics  economic history  and law and economics    Spring 2011 Newsletter  Field Test  Faculty Research  TAPS  New Faculty  Lopez Chair  Alumni in the News  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  BGS   ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   New Faculty Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   New Faculty Home Academics Areas of Study Social Science Economics   Business New Faculty      New Faculty Jeff Smith joins us after finishing a 21 year career in the United States Air Force  Jeff s educational credentials consist of a B A  in economics from the University of South Carolina  a M S  in Applied Economics from Wright State University  and a Ph D  in Economics from the University of Tennessee  Jeff is married to Lisa Smith  and they have two boys  Jeffrey and Phillip  ages 17 and 16 respectively  Jeff s career in the Air Force spanned three different occupational specialties and two continents  He started as a second lieutenant ICBM missile launcher officer  spent approximately ten years working in various financial managements jobs both in the U S  and Germany  and for the last ten years he was either in school or teaching  first at the Air Force s graduate school  and finally at the United States Air Force Academy  Jennifer E  Gerow earned a Ph D  in Management  concentration  Information Systems  from Clemson University  She also has an MBA and a Bachelor of Science in Biological Sciences with a minor in Secondary Education  She has 9 years of industry experience in e commerce  Her research int